rEvent - a distributed event system
a RadicalDesigns project

This source code is released under the GNU General Public License:
http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html

rEvent is a web application written using ruby on rails.  Its primary
purpose is to allows users to organize events occurring nation-wide
to provide solidarity to a movement.

rEvent has four distinct stages:
  1. Setup 
  2. Users signup to host an event.
  3. Users search for events (using map) and RSVP
  4. After event occurrs, users report-back with text, images and YouTube embeds.
